**Example 6**: If \(n\) is a positive integer, prove that \((-1+\mathrm{i}\sqrt{3})^{n}+(-1-\mathrm{i}\sqrt{3})^{n}=2^{n\star 1}\cos\left( \frac{2n\pi}{3}\right)\).

**Solution**

\(\left|-1+\mathrm{i}\sqrt{3}\right|=2\), \(\arg(-1+\mathrm{i}\sqrt{3})=\frac{2\pi}{3}\)\(\Rightarrow\)\(-1+\mathrm{i}\sqrt{3}=2\mathrm{e}^{\frac{2\pi}{3}}\)

Since \(-1-\mathrm{i}\sqrt{3}\) and \(-1+\mathrm{i}\sqrt{3}\) are conjugates of each other, \(-1-\mathrm{i}\sqrt{3}=2\mathrm{e}^{-\frac{2\pi}{3}}\)

Now \((-1+\mathrm{i}\sqrt{3})^{n}+(-1-\mathrm{i}\sqrt{3})^{n}=\left(2\mathrm{e}^{ \frac{12\pi}{3}}\right)^{n}+\left(2\mathrm{e}^{-\frac{12\pi}{3}}\right)^{n}\)

\(=2^{n}\left(\mathrm{e}^{\frac{12\pi\pi}{3}}\right)+2^{n}\left(\mathrm{e}^{- \frac{12\pi\pi}{3}}\right)\)

\(=2^{n}\left(\mathrm{e}^{\frac{12\pi\pi}{3}}+\mathrm{e}^{-\frac{12\pi\pi}{3}}\right)\)

\(=2^{n}\times 2\) Re\(\left(\mathrm{e}^{\frac{12\pi\pi}{3}}\right)\)

since \(z+z^{\star}=2\) Re\((z)\)

\(=2^{n\star 1}\cos\frac{2n\pi}{3}\)

