Euler's Formula

\[\cos\theta+\mathrm{i}\sin\theta=\mathrm{e}^{\mathrm{i}\theta}\]

Proof:

From the series expansions of \(\mathrm{e}^{\theta},\cos\theta\) and \(\sin\theta\) (which will be covered in Chapter 7D), we have

\[\mathrm{e}^{\mathrm{i}\theta}= 1+\mathrm{i}\theta+\frac{(\mathrm{i}\theta)^{2}}{2!}+\frac{( \mathrm{i}\theta)^{3}}{3!}+\frac{(\mathrm{i}\theta)^{4}}{4!}+\frac{(\mathrm{i} \theta)^{5}}{5!}+...\] \[= 1+\mathrm{i}\theta-\frac{\theta^{2}}{2!}-\mathrm{i}\frac{\theta ^{3}}{3!}+\frac{\theta^{4}}{4!}+\mathrm{i}\frac{\theta^{5}}{5!}+...\] \[\quad\quad\quad(\mathrm{using~{}the~{}result~{}that~{}if~{}}k\in \mathbb{Z}^{*}\,,\,\mathrm{i}^{44}= 1,\,\,\,\,\mathrm{i}^{44+1}=\mathrm{i},\,\,\,\mathrm{i}^{44+2}=-\mathrm{i},\, \,\,\mathrm{i}^{44+3}=-\mathrm{i}\,)\] \[= \left(1-\frac{\theta^{2}}{2!}+\frac{\theta^{4}}{4!}-...\right) +\mathrm{i}\left(\theta-\frac{\theta^{3}}{3!}+\frac{\theta^{5}}{5!}-...\right)\] \[= \cos\theta+\mathrm{i}\sin\theta\]

